Somali Pirates Free Oil Tanker Zirku After Ransom Payment, Ecoterra Says

-- B y   A l a r i c   N i g h t i n g a l e
-- 
2011-06-13T07:44:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/somali-pirates-free-oil-tanker-zirku-after-ransom-payment-ecoterra-says.html
Somali pirates released the crude-
oil tanker Zirku after a ransom payment was made, according to
Ecoterra International, an environmental group that monitors
piracy.  The vessel was freed 45 days after its seizure, Espenau,
Germany-based Ecoterra said in a June 11 e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaric Nightingale in London at 
 anightingale@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stuart Wallace at   swallace6@bloomberg.net  